teenth century-pearlers had stripped riverbeds of mussels, mushroom pickers had uprooted the steppe, and fur-bearing animals had disappeared from the forest. In response, the court turned to "purification;" it registered and arrested poachers, reformed territorial rule, and redefined the boundary between the pristine and the corrupted. Schlesinger's resulting analysis provides a framework for rethinking the global invention of nature.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 23. Jul 2020) 0aLuxurieszChinaxHistoryy18th century. 0aLuxurieszChinaxHistoryy19th century. 0aNatural resourceszChinazManchuriaxHistory. 0aNatural resourceszMongoliaxHistory. 0aRestoration ecologyzChinazManchuriaxHistory. 0aRestoration ecologyzMongoliaxHistory. 4aChina. 4aEmpire. 4aEnvironmental History. 4aHistory. 4aManchuria. 4aMongolia. 4aNature. 4aQing. 7aHISTORY / Asia / China.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUP Complete eBook-Package 2017z978311070369640uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781503600683zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781503600683423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781503600683.jpg  a978-3-11-070369-6  SUP Complete eBook-Package 2017b2017  aGBV-deGruyter-alles